description:
OFFICER: &ldquo;Captain! What&rsquo;s that?&rdquo;
CAPTAIN: &ldquo;Dear God! Something&rsquo;s torn that
planet in half!&rdquo;
OFFICER: &ldquo;We&rsquo;re taking damage from the
debris.&rdquo;
CAPTAIN: &ldquo;Take evasive manoeuvres!&rdquo;
OFFICER: &ldquo;I&rsquo;m picking up multiple life forms
spawning from the epicentre.&rdquo;
CAPTAIN: &ldquo;That&rsquo;s the Skurge! A self replicating
biological nightmare destined to consume
every other living entity! We need to get to
Earth and warn them. There&rsquo;s a jump gate 5
systems away; set a course!&rdquo;
OFFICER: &ldquo;What about the outer colonies?&rdquo;
CAPTAIN: &ldquo;We&rsquo;ll have to save what we can.
Let&rsquo;s GO! GO! GO!&rdquo;

An entity of pure evil, known as the Skurge, has been released and now it's played job to reach the jump gate at the end of the map.

In the game, each turn you race across the map, collecting resources and spending resources to gain better items.  At the end of the game, the player with the most valuable items wins.

You start the game at the planet where the Skurge appear.  On your turn you will move to the next planet.  Sometimes you have a choice of which planet to move to. If the planet has not been visited you will only see partial information about what resources you may need at that planet.

Once at the planet you will execute one of the three action tracks available to you.  These actions will sometimes give you resources, or you may need to spend resources to obtain more valuable items or repair your ship.

After the actions have been performed, the Skurge advance.  If the Skurge reach a player's location, they are eliminated and the game ends.

So it's imperative that you both make it to the jump gate before the Skurge get you!

&mdash;description from the designer

Це Бізнес Крихітка ("This is Business Baby") is a board game with unique mechanics for those who want to learn financial literacy, improve their time management skills, and plunge into the world of entrepreneurship.

The game has a completely unique methodology and is based on the "win-win" strategy, where the most important thing is not victory, but the analysis of your actions during the game and interaction with other players.

In a playful way, you:

     learn about the methods of earning;
     organize your own business;
     get the necessary skills to start your own business;
     understand the importance of the resource of time;
     train your creative thinking skills;
     make your dream come true.

&ldquo;Space Travel Dice: The storytelling game with nine wooden dice.&rdquo;

&ldquo;Revive the art of storytelling using these nine illustrated wooden dice to create intergalactic adventures. Includes superhuman powers that will make your heroes utterly invincible! Ideal for playing by a log fire, this game will stimulate the imaginations of children and adults alike.&rdquo;

Rules:
Any number of players.
Roll all eight of the mainly black-sided dice.  Begin telling a story based on the images you rolled. Save the the red-sided die for later rolling and use. Each of the eight mainly black-sided dice have one red &lsquo;@&lsquo; symbol.  This allows you to roll the red die and get a super power based on what you roll.  You can get multiple powers in a story and the build.

You can try telling the story in single die roll sequence or create the story collaboratively by taking turns rolling and adding to the story.
